<subSubSection id="C36B652A8150FFFCFF31F90AFE16F892" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCE36A18150FFFCFF31F90AFBECF906" blockId="127.[136,1452,1686,1857]" box="[189,1119,1722,1749]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B905EAB38150FFFCFF31F90AFEC6F906" bold="true" box="[189,373,1722,1748]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Distribution:—</emphasis>
Northern 
<collectingCountry id="F36676318150FFFCFE6DF90BFDE3F907" box="[481,592,1723,1749]" name="Myanmar" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, southwestern and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F36676318150FFFCFC00F90AFC7CF906" box="[908,975,1722,1748]" name="China" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F36676318150FFFCFB89F90AFBE8F906" box="[1029,1115,1722,1748]" name="Taiwan" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE36A18150FFFCFF31F96EFE16F892" blockId="127.[136,1452,1686,1857]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B905EAB38150FFFCFF31F96EFEA8F92A" bold="true" box="[189,283,1758,1784]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Note:—</emphasis>
In 
<emphasis id="B905EAB38150FFFCFEB4F96EFE6DF92A" box="[312,478,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
Flora of 
<collectingCountry id="F36676318150FFFCFE16F96EFE6DF92A" box="[410,478,1758,1784]" name="China" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">China</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, this entity was considered conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D228150FFFCFC42F96FFB57F92A" authority="(Lindl.) Schltr." authorityName="Schltr." baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[974,1252,1758,1785]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Erythrodes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blumei">
<emphasis id="B905EAB38150FFFCFC42F96FFB8BF92A" box="[974,1080,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">E. blumei</emphasis>
(Lindl.) Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
because variation among the two in spur length and epichile shape were apparently continuous (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B508150FFFCFC62F8B2FAB0F8CF" author="Chen, S. C. &amp; Liu, Z. J. &amp; Zhu, G. H. &amp; Lang, K. Y. &amp; Tsi, Z. H. &amp; Luo, Y. B. &amp; Jin, X. H. &amp; Cribb, P. J. &amp; Wood, J. J. &amp; Gale, S. W. &amp; Ormerod, P. &amp; Vermeulen, J. J. &amp; Wood, H. P. &amp; Clayton, D. &amp; Bell, A." box="[1006,1283,1794,1821]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" refId="ref221945" refString="Chen, S. C., Liu, Z. J., Zhu, G. H., Lang, K. Y., Tsi, Z. H., Luo, Y. B., Jin, X. H., Cribb, P. J., Wood, J. J., Gale, S. W., Ormerod, P., Vermeulen, J. J., Wood, H. P., Clayton, D. &amp; Bell, A. (2009) Orchidaceae. In: Wu, Z. Y., Raven, P. H. &amp; Hong, D. Y. (Eds.), Flora of China, vol. 25. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis, 570 pp." type="book" year="2009">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B905EAB38150FFFCFBBDF8B3FBDAF8CE" box="[1073,1129,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">et al.</emphasis>
2009: 56−57
</bibRefCitation>
). Further study to confirm this is needed.
</paragraph>
